"Abstract One loss is good for the soul. Too many losses are not good for the coach. Knute Rockne Take any time period during the past decade. There has been a rapidly increasing upward trend in both the number and intensity of information warfare (IW) attacks. No matter how you slice and dice the numbers, relative and absolute losses from IW attacks are lowering corporate profits. After a number of adjustments have failed to produce a winning effort, any good coach will return to the basics to review and overhaul outdated approaches."
